55 void PrintDouble(std::ostream& os, double val) {
56  if (i::IsMinusZero(val)) {
57  os << "-0.0";
58  } else if (val == DoubleToInteger(val) && val >= kMinSafeInteger &&
59  val <= kMaxSafeInteger) {
60  // Print integer HeapNumbers in safe integer range with max precision: as
61  // 9007199254740991.0 instead of 9.0072e+15
62  int64_t i = static_cast<int64_t>(val);
63  os << i << ".0";
64  } else {
65  os << val;
66  }
67 }

72 void Print(Tagged<Object> obj) {
73  // Output into debugger's command window if a debugger is attached.
74  DbgStdoutStream dbg_os;
75  Print(obj, dbg_os);
76  dbg_os << std::flush;
77 
78  StdoutStream os;
79  Print(obj, os);
80  os << std::flush;
81 }

83 void Print(Tagged<Object> obj, std::ostream& os) {
84  if (IsSmi(obj)) {
85  os << "Smi: " << std::hex << "0x" << Smi::ToInt(obj);
86  os << std::dec << " (" << Smi::ToInt(obj) << ")\n";
87  } else {
88  Cast<HeapObject>(obj)->HeapObjectPrint(os);
89  }
90 }

94 #define AS_PTR(x) reinterpret_cast<void*>(x)
95 #define AS_OBJ(x) Brief(Tagged<Object>(x))
96 
97 void PrintFunctionCallbackInfo(Address* implicit_args, Address* js_args,
98  Address length, std::ostream& os) {
99  using FCA = FunctionCallbackArguments;
100 
101  static_assert(FCA::kArgsLength == 6);
102  os << "FunctionCallbackInfo: " //
103  << "\n - isolate: " << AS_PTR(implicit_args[FCA::kIsolateIndex])
104  << "\n - return_value: " << AS_OBJ(implicit_args[FCA::kReturnValueIndex])
105  << "\n - target: " << AS_OBJ(implicit_args[FCA::kTargetIndex])
106  << "\n - new_target: " << AS_OBJ(implicit_args[FCA::kNewTargetIndex])
107 
108  << "\n - argc: " << length //
109  << "\n - receiver: " << AS_OBJ(js_args[0]);
110 
111  constexpr int kMaxArgs = 4;
112  for (int i = 0; i < std::min(static_cast<int>(length), kMaxArgs); i++) {
113  os << "\n - arg[" << i << "]: " << AS_OBJ(js_args[i]);
114  }
115  os << "\n";
116 }
117 
118 void PrintPropertyCallbackInfo(Address* args, std::ostream& os) {
119  using PCA = internal::PropertyCallbackArguments;
120 
121  static_assert(PCA::kArgsLength == 8);
122  os << "PropertyCallbackInfo: " //
123  << "\n - isolate: " << AS_PTR(args[PCA::kIsolateIndex])
124  << "\n - return_value: " << AS_OBJ(args[PCA::kReturnValueIndex])
125  << "\n - should_throw: " << AS_OBJ(args[PCA::kShouldThrowOnErrorIndex])
126  << "\n - holder: " << AS_OBJ(args[PCA::kHolderIndex])
127  << "\n - holderV2: " << AS_OBJ(args[PCA::kHolderV2Index])
128  << "\n - data: " << AS_OBJ(args[PCA::kDataIndex]) //
129  << "\n - property_key: " << AS_OBJ(args[PCA::kPropertyKeyIndex])
130  << "\n - receiver: " << AS_OBJ(args[PCA::kThisIndex]);
131 
132  // In case it's a setter call there will be additional |value| parameter,
133  // print it as a raw pointer to avoid crashing.
134  os << "\n - value?: " << AS_PTR(args[PCA::kArgsLength]);
135  os << "\n";
136 }
137 
138 #undef AS_PTR
139 #undef AS_OBJ

143 void PrintFunctionCallbackInfo(void* function_callback_info) {
144  using FCI = v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>;
145  FCI& info = *reinterpret_cast<FCI*>(function_callback_info);
146 
147  // |values| points to the first argument after the receiver.
148  Address* js_args = info.values_ - 1;
149 
150  // Output into debugger's command window if a debugger is attached.
151  DbgStdoutStream dbg_os;
152  PrintFunctionCallbackInfo(info.implicit_args_, js_args, info.length_, dbg_os);
153  dbg_os << std::flush;
154 
155  StdoutStream os;
156  PrintFunctionCallbackInfo(info.implicit_args_, js_args, info.length_, os);
157  os << std::flush;
158 }

160 void PrintPropertyCallbackInfo(void* property_callback_info) {
161  using PCI = v8::PropertyCallbackInfo<v8::Value>;
162  PCI& info = *reinterpret_cast<PCI*>(property_callback_info);
163 
164  // Output into debugger's command window if a debugger is attached.
165  DbgStdoutStream dbg_os;
166  PrintPropertyCallbackInfo(info.args_, dbg_os);
167  dbg_os << std::flush;
168 
169  StdoutStream os;
170  PrintPropertyCallbackInfo(info.args_, os);
171  os << std::flush;
172 }

176 void PrintHeapObjectHeaderWithoutMap(Tagged<HeapObject> object,
177  std::ostream& os, const char* id) {
178  PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase();
179  os << reinterpret_cast<void*>(object.ptr()) << ": [";
180  if (id != nullptr) {
181  os << id;
182  } else {
183  os << object->map(cage_base)->instance_type();
184  }
185  os << "]";
186  if (ReadOnlyHeap::Contains(object)) {
187  os << " in ReadOnlySpace";
188  } else if (Isolate::Current()->heap()->InOldSpace(object)) {
189  os << " in OldSpace";
190  } else if (HeapLayout::InAnySharedSpace(object)) {
191  os << " in SharedSpace";
192  }
193 }

195 template <typename T>
196 void PrintDictionaryContents(std::ostream& os, Tagged<T> dict) {
197  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
198  ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
199 
200  if (dict->Capacity() == 0) {
201  return;
202  }
203 
204 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY
205  Isolate* isolate = GetIsolateFromWritableObject(dict);
206  // IterateEntries for SwissNameDictionary needs to create a handle.
207  HandleScope scope(isolate);
208 #endif
209  for (InternalIndex i : dict->IterateEntries()) {
210  Tagged<Object> k;
211  if (!dict->ToKey(roots, i, &k)) continue;
212  os << "\n ";
213  if (IsString(k)) {
214  Cast<String>(k)->PrintUC16(os);
215  } else {
216  os << Brief(k);
217  }
218  os << ": " << Brief(dict->ValueAt(i)) << " ";
219  dict->DetailsAt(i).PrintAsSlowTo(os, !T::kIsOrderedDictionaryType);
220  }
221 }
222 } // namespace

228 void HeapObject::PrintHeader(std::ostream& os, const char* id) {
229  PrintHeapObjectHeaderWithoutMap(*this, os, id);
230  PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase();
231  if (!SafeEquals(GetReadOnlyRoots().meta_map())) {
232  os << "\n - map: " << Brief(map(cage_base));
233  }
234 }

236 void HeapObject::HeapObjectPrint(std::ostream& os) {
237  PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase();
238 
239  InstanceType instance_type = map(cage_base)->instance_type();
240 
241  if (instance_type < FIRST_NONSTRING_TYPE) {
242  Cast<String>(*this)->StringPrint(os);
243  os << "\n";
244  return;
245  }
246 
247  // Skip invalid trusted objects. Technically it'd be fine to still handle
248  // them below since we only print the objects, but such an object will
249  // quickly lead to out-of-sandbox segfaults and so fuzzers will complain.
250  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsTrustedObject(instance_type) &&
251  !OutsideSandboxOrInReadonlySpace(*this)) {
252  os << "<Invalid TrustedObject (outside trusted space)>\n";
253  return;
254  }
255 
256  switch (instance_type) {
257  case AWAIT_CONTEXT_TYPE:
258  case BLOCK_CONTEXT_TYPE:
259  case CATCH_CONTEXT_TYPE:
260  case DEBUG_EVALUATE_CONTEXT_TYPE:
261  case EVAL_CONTEXT_TYPE:
262  case FUNCTION_CONTEXT_TYPE:
263  case MODULE_CONTEXT_TYPE:
264  case SCRIPT_CONTEXT_TYPE:
265  case WITH_CONTEXT_TYPE:
266  Cast<Context>(*this)->ContextPrint(os);
267  break;
268  case NATIVE_CONTEXT_TYPE:
269  Cast<NativeContext>(*this)->NativeContextPrint(os);
270  break;
271  case HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
272  Cast<ObjectHashTable>(*this)->ObjectHashTablePrint(os);
273  break;
274  case DOUBLE_STRING_CACHE_TYPE:
275  Cast<DoubleStringCache>(*this)->DoubleStringCachePrint(os);
276  break;
277  case NAME_TO_INDEX_HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
278  Cast<NameToIndexHashTable>(*this)->NameToIndexHashTablePrint(os);
279  break;
280  case REGISTERED_SYMBOL_TABLE_TYPE:
281  Cast<RegisteredSymbolTable>(*this)->RegisteredSymbolTablePrint(os);
282  break;
283  case ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE:
284  Cast<OrderedHashMap>(*this)->OrderedHashMapPrint(os);
285  break;
286  case ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE:
287  Cast<OrderedHashSet>(*this)->OrderedHashSetPrint(os);
288  break;
289  case ORDERED_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
290  Cast<OrderedNameDictionary>(*this)->OrderedNameDictionaryPrint(os);
291  break;
292  case NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
293  Cast<NameDictionary>(*this)->NameDictionaryPrint(os);
294  break;
295  case GLOBAL_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
296  Cast<GlobalDictionary>(*this)->GlobalDictionaryPrint(os);
297  break;
298  case SIMPLE_NAME_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
299  Cast<FixedArray>(*this)->FixedArrayPrint(os);
300  break;
301  case SIMPLE_NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
302  Cast<FixedArray>(*this)->FixedArrayPrint(os);
303  break;
304  case NUMBER_DICTIONARY_TYPE:
305  Cast<NumberDictionary>(*this)->NumberDictionaryPrint(os);
306  break;
307  case EPHEMERON_HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
308  Cast<EphemeronHashTable>(*this)->EphemeronHashTablePrint(os);
309  break;
310  case TRANSITION_ARRAY_TYPE:
311  Cast<TransitionArray>(*this)->TransitionArrayPrint(os);
312  break;
313  case FILLER_TYPE:
314  os << "filler";
315  break;
316  case JS_API_OBJECT_TYPE:
317  case JS_ARRAY_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
318  case JS_CONTEXT_EXTENSION_OBJECT_TYPE:
319  case JS_ERROR_TYPE:
320  case JS_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
321  case JS_MAP_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
322  case JS_OBJECT_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
323  case JS_PROMISE_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
324  case JS_REG_EXP_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
325  case JS_SET_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
326  case JS_SET_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
327  case JS_SPECIAL_API_OBJECT_TYPE:
328  case JS_STRING_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
329  case JS_TYPED_ARRAY_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
330  Cast<JSObject>(*this)->JSObjectPrint(os);
331  break;
332 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
333  case WASM_TRUSTED_INSTANCE_DATA_TYPE:
334  Cast<WasmTrustedInstanceData>(*this)->WasmTrustedInstanceDataPrint(os);
335  break;
336  case WASM_DISPATCH_TABLE_TYPE:
337  Cast<WasmDispatchTable>(*this)->WasmDispatchTablePrint(os);
338  break;
339  case WASM_VALUE_OBJECT_TYPE:
340  Cast<WasmValueObject>(*this)->WasmValueObjectPrint(os);
341  break;
342  case WASM_EXCEPTION_PACKAGE_TYPE:
343  Cast<WasmExceptionPackage>(*this)->WasmExceptionPackagePrint(os);
344  break;
345 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
346  case INSTRUCTION_STREAM_TYPE:
347  Cast<InstructionStream>(*this)->InstructionStreamPrint(os);
348  break;
349  case CODE_TYPE:
350  Cast<Code>(*this)->CodePrint(os);
351  break;
352  case CODE_WRAPPER_TYPE:
353  Cast<CodeWrapper>(*this)->CodeWrapperPrint(os);
354  break;
355  case JS_SET_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
356  case JS_SET_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
357  Cast<JSSetIterator>(*this)->JSSetIteratorPrint(os);
358  break;
359  case JS_MAP_KEY_ITERATOR_TYPE:
360  case JS_MAP_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
361  case JS_MAP_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
362  Cast<JSMapIterator>(*this)->JSMapIteratorPrint(os);
363  break;
364 #define MAKE_TORQUE_CASE(Name, TYPE) \
365  case TYPE: \
366  Cast<Name>(*this)->Name##Print(os); \
367  break;
368  // Every class that has its fields defined in a .tq file and corresponds
369  // to exactly one InstanceType value is included in the following list.
370  TORQUE_INSTANCE_CHECKERS_SINGLE_FULLY_DEFINED(MAKE_TORQUE_CASE)
371  TORQUE_INSTANCE_CHECKERS_MULTIPLE_FULLY_DEFINED(MAKE_TORQUE_CASE)
372 #undef MAKE_TORQUE_CASE
373 
374  case TUPLE2_TYPE:
375  Cast<Tuple2>(*this)->Tuple2Print(os);
376  break;
377  case CLASS_POSITIONS_TYPE:
378  Cast<ClassPositions>(*this)->ClassPositionsPrint(os);
379  break;
380  case ACCESSOR_PAIR_TYPE:
381  Cast<AccessorPair>(*this)->AccessorPairPrint(os);
382  break;
383  case ALLOCATION_SITE_TYPE:
384  Cast<AllocationSite>(*this)->AllocationSitePrint(os);
385  break;
386  case LOAD_HANDLER_TYPE:
387  Cast<LoadHandler>(*this)->LoadHandlerPrint(os);
388  break;
389  case STORE_HANDLER_TYPE:
390  Cast<StoreHandler>(*this)->StoreHandlerPrint(os);
391  break;
392  case FEEDBACK_METADATA_TYPE:
393  Cast<FeedbackMetadata>(*this)->FeedbackMetadataPrint(os);
394  break;
395  case BIG_INT_BASE_TYPE:
396  Cast<BigIntBase>(*this)->BigIntBasePrint(os);
397  break;
398  case FREE_SPACE_TYPE:
399  Cast<FreeSpace>(*this)->FreeSpacePrint(os);
400  break;
401  case JS_CLASS_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
402  case JS_PROMISE_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
403  case JS_REG_EXP_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
404  case JS_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
405 #define TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTORS_SWITCH(Type, type, TYPE, Ctype) \
406  case TYPE##_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
407  TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTORS_SWITCH)
408 #undef TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTORS_SWITCH
409  Cast<JSFunction>(*this)->JSFunctionPrint(os);
410  break;
411  case INTERNALIZED_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
412  case EXTERNAL_INTERNALIZED_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
413  case INTERNALIZED_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
414  case EXTERNAL_INTERNALIZED_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
415  case UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_INTERNALIZED_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
416  case UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_INTERNALIZED_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
417  case SEQ_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
418  case CONS_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
419  case EXTERNAL_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
420  case SLICED_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
421  case THIN_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
422  case SEQ_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
423  case CONS_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
424  case EXTERNAL_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
425  case SLICED_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
426  case THIN_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
427  case UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
428  case UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
429  case SHARED_SEQ_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
430  case SHARED_SEQ_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
431  case SHARED_EXTERNAL_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
432  case SHARED_EXTERNAL_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
433  case SHARED_UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
434  case SHARED_UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
435  case JS_LAST_DUMMY_API_OBJECT_TYPE:
436  // TODO(all): Handle these types too.
437  os << "UNKNOWN TYPE " << map()->instance_type();
438  UNREACHABLE();
439  }
440 }

442 template <typename T>
443 void PrintByteArrayElements(std::ostream& os, const T* array) {
444  int length = array->length();
445  int i = 0;
446  while (i < length) {
447  os << " 0x" << std::setfill('0') << std::setw(4) << std::hex << i << ":";
448  int line_end = std::min(i + 16, length);
449  for (; i < line_end; ++i) {
450  os << " " << std::setfill('0') << std::setw(2) << std::hex
451  << static_cast<int>(array->get(i));
452  }
453  os << "\n";
454  }
455 }

487 bool JSObject::PrintProperties(std::ostream& os) {
488  if (HasFastProperties()) {
489  Tagged<DescriptorArray> descs =
490  map()->instance_descriptors(Isolate::Current());
491  int nof_inobject_properties = map()->GetInObjectProperties();
492  for (InternalIndex i : map()->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
493  os << "\n ";
494  descs->GetKey(i)->NamePrint(os);
495  os << ": ";
496  PropertyDetails details = descs->GetDetails(i);
497  switch (details.location()) {
498  case PropertyLocation::kField: {
499  FieldIndex field_index = FieldIndex::ForDetails(map(), details);
500  os << Brief(RawFastPropertyAt(field_index));
501  break;
502  }
503  case PropertyLocation::kDescriptor:
504  os << Brief(descs->GetStrongValue(i));
505  break;
506  }
507  os << " ";
508  details.PrintAsFastTo(os, PropertyDetails::kForProperties);
509  if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
510  os << " @ ";
511  FieldType::PrintTo(descs->GetFieldType(i), os);
512  int field_index = details.field_index();
513  if (field_index < nof_inobject_properties) {
514  os << ", location: in-object";
515  } else {
516  field_index -= nof_inobject_properties;
517  os << ", location: properties[" << field_index << "]";
518  }
519  } else {
520  os << ", location: descriptor";
521  }
522  }
523  return map()->NumberOfOwnDescriptors() > 0;
524  } else if (IsJSGlobalObject(*this)) {
525  PrintDictionaryContents(
526  os, Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*this)->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad));
527  } else if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
528  PrintDictionaryContents(os, property_dictionary_swiss());
529  } else {
530  PrintDictionaryContents(os, property_dictionary());
531  }
532  return true;
533 }

539  return false;

542 template <>
543 bool IsTheHoleAt(Tagged<FixedDoubleArray> array, int index) {
544  return array->is_the_hole(index);
545 }

559 template <class T>
560 double GetScalarElement(Tagged<T> array, int index) {
561  if (IsTheHoleAt(array, index)) {
562  return std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
563  }
564  return array->get_scalar(index);
565 }
566 
567 template <class T>
568 void DoPrintElements(std::ostream& os, Tagged<Object> object, int length) {
569  const bool print_the_hole = std::is_same_v<T, FixedDoubleArray>;
570  Tagged<T> array = Cast<T>(object);
571  if (length == 0) return;
572  int previous_index = 0;
573  uint64_t previous_representation = array->get_representation(0);
574  uint64_t representation = 0;
575  int i;
576  for (i = 1; i <= length; i++) {
577  if (i < length) {
578  representation = array->get_representation(i);
579  if (previous_representation == representation) continue;
580  }
581  os << "\n";
582  std::stringstream ss;
583  ss << previous_index;
584  if (previous_index != i - 1) {
585  ss << '-' << (i - 1);
586  }
587  os << std::setw(12) << ss.str() << ": ";
588  if (print_the_hole && IsTheHoleAt(array, i - 1)) {
589  os << "<the_hole>";
590 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
591  } else if (IsUndefinedAt(array, i - 1)) {
592  os << "undefined";
593 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
594  } else {
595  os << GetScalarElement(array, i - 1);
596  }
597  previous_index = i;
598  previous_representation = representation;
599  }
600 }
601 
602 struct Fp16Printer {
603  uint16_t val;
604  explicit Fp16Printer(float f) : val(fp16_ieee_from_fp32_value(f)) {}
605  operator float() const { return fp16_ieee_to_fp32_value(val); }
606 };
607 
608 template <typename ElementType>
609 void PrintTypedArrayElements(std::ostream& os, const ElementType* data_ptr,
610  size_t length, bool is_on_heap) {
611  if (length == 0) return;
612  size_t previous_index = 0;
613  if (i::v8_flags.mock_arraybuffer_allocator && !is_on_heap) {
614  // Don't try to print data that's not actually allocated.
615  os << "\n 0-" << length << ": <mocked array buffer bytes>";
616  return;
617  }
618 
619  ElementType previous_value = data_ptr[0];
620  ElementType value{0};
621  for (size_t i = 1; i <= length; i++) {
622  if (i < length) value = data_ptr[i];
623  if (i != length && previous_value == value) {
624  continue;
625  }
626  os << "\n";
627  std::stringstream ss;
628  ss << previous_index;
629  if (previous_index != i - 1) {
630  ss << '-' << (i - 1);
631  }
632  os << std::setw(12) << ss.str() << ": " << +previous_value;
633  previous_index = i;
634  previous_value = value;
635  }
636 }
637 
638 template <typename T>
639 void PrintFixedArrayElements(std::ostream& os, Tagged<T> array, int capacity,
640  Tagged<Object> (*get)(Tagged<T>, int)) {
641  // Print in array notation for non-sparse arrays.
642  if (capacity == 0) return;
643  Tagged<Object> previous_value = get(array, 0);
644  Tagged<Object> value;
645  int previous_index = 0;
646  int i;
647  for (i = 1; i <= capacity; i++) {
648  if (i < capacity) value = get(array, i);
649  if (previous_value == value && i != capacity) {
650  continue;
651  }
652  os << "\n";
653  std::stringstream ss;
654  ss << previous_index;
655  if (previous_index != i - 1) {
656  ss << '-' << (i - 1);
657  }
658  os << std::setw(12) << ss.str() << ": " << Brief(previous_value);
659  previous_index = i;
660  previous_value = value;
661  }
662 }
663

665 void PrintFixedArrayElements(std::ostream& os, Tagged<T> array) {
666  PrintFixedArrayElements<T>(
667  os, array, array->length(),
668  [](Tagged<T> xs, int i) { return Cast<Object>(xs->get(i)); });
669 }

683 void PrintSloppyArgumentElements(std::ostream& os, ElementsKind kind,
684  Tagged<SloppyArgumentsElements> elements) {
685  Tagged<FixedArray> arguments_store = elements->arguments();
686  os << "\n 0: context: " << Brief(elements->context())
687  << "\n 1: arguments_store: " << Brief(arguments_store)
688  << "\n parameter to context slot map:";
689  for (int i = 0; i < elements->length(); i++) {
690  Tagged<Object> mapped_entry = elements->mapped_entries(i, kRelaxedLoad);
691  os << "\n " << i << ": param(" << i << "): " << Brief(mapped_entry);
692  if (IsTheHole(mapped_entry)) {
693  os << " in the arguments_store[" << i << "]";
694  } else {
695  os << " in the context";
696  }
697  }
698  if (arguments_store->length() == 0) return;
699  os << "\n }"
700  << "\n - arguments_store: " << Brief(arguments_store) << " "
701  << ElementsKindToString(arguments_store->map()->elements_kind()) << " {";
702  if (kind == FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS) {
703  PrintFixedArrayElements(os, arguments_store);
704  } else {
705  DCHECK_EQ(kind, SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS);
706  PrintDictionaryElements(os, arguments_store);
707  }
708 }

723 void JSObject::PrintElements(std::ostream& os) {
724  // Don't call GetElementsKind, its validation code can cause the printer to
725  // fail when debugging.
726  os << " - elements: " << Brief(elements()) << " {";
727  switch (map()->elements_kind()) {
728  case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
729  case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
730  case HOLEY_ELEMENTS:
731  case HOLEY_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
732  case HOLEY_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
733  case HOLEY_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
734  case PACKED_ELEMENTS:
735  case PACKED_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
736  case PACKED_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
737  case PACKED_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
738  case FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
739  case SHARED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS: {
740  PrintFixedArrayElements(os, Cast<FixedArray>(elements()));
741  break;
742  }
743  case HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
744  case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS: {
745  DoPrintElements<FixedDoubleArray>(os, elements(), elements()->length());
746  break;
747  }
748 
749 #define PRINT_ELEMENTS(Type, type, TYPE, elementType) \
750  case TYPE##_ELEMENTS: { \
751  size_t length = Cast<JSTypedArray>(*this)->GetLength(); \
752  bool is_on_heap = Cast<JSTypedArray>(*this)->is_on_heap(); \
753  const elementType* data_ptr = \
754  static_cast<const elementType*>(Cast<JSTypedArray>(*this)->DataPtr()); \
755  PrintTypedArrayElements<elementType>(os, data_ptr, length, is_on_heap); \
756  break; \
757  }
758  TYPED_ARRAYS(PRINT_ELEMENTS)
759  RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(PRINT_ELEMENTS)
760 #undef PRINT_ELEMENTS
761 
762  case DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS:
763  case SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
764  PrintDictionaryElements(os, elements());
765  break;
766  case FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
767  case SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
768  PrintSloppyArgumentElements(os, map()->elements_kind(),
769  Cast<SloppyArgumentsElements>(elements()));
770  break;
771  case WASM_ARRAY_ELEMENTS:
772  // WasmArrayPrint() should be called instead.
773  UNREACHABLE();
774  case NO_ELEMENTS:
775  break;
776  }
777  os << "\n }\n";
778 }

782 void JSObjectPrintHeader(std::ostream& os, Tagged<JSObject> obj,
783  const char* id) {
784  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
785  obj->PrintHeader(os, id);
786  // Don't call GetElementsKind, its validation code can cause the printer to
787  // fail when debugging.
788  os << " [";
789  if (obj->HasFastProperties()) {
790  os << "FastProperties";
791  } else {
792  os << "DictionaryProperties";
793  }
794  PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, obj);
795  os << "]\n - prototype: " << Brief(iter.GetCurrent());
796  os << "\n - elements: " << Brief(obj->elements()) << " ["
797  << ElementsKindToString(obj->map()->elements_kind());
798  if (obj->elements()->IsCowArray()) os << " (COW)";
799  os << "]";
800  Tagged<Object> hash = Object::GetHash(obj);
801  if (IsSmi(hash)) {
802  os << "\n - hash: " << Brief(hash);
803  }
804  if (obj->GetEmbedderFieldCount() > 0) {
805  os << "\n - embedder fields: " << obj->GetEmbedderFieldCount();
806  }
807 }

818 void JSObjectPrintBody(std::ostream& os, Tagged<JSObject> obj,
819  bool print_elements = true) {
820  os << "\n - properties: ";
821  Tagged<Object> properties_or_hash = obj->raw_properties_or_hash(kRelaxedLoad);
822  if (!IsSmi(properties_or_hash)) {
823  os << Brief(properties_or_hash);
824  }
825  os << "\n - All own properties (excluding elements): {";
826  if (obj->PrintProperties(os)) os << "\n ";
827  os << "}\n";
828 
829  if (print_elements) {
830  size_t length = IsJSTypedArray(obj) ? Cast<JSTypedArray>(obj)->GetLength()
831  : obj->elements()->length();
832  if (length > 0) obj->PrintElements(os);
833  }
834  int embedder_fields = obj->GetEmbedderFieldCount();
835  if (embedder_fields > 0) {
836  IsolateForSandbox isolate = GetCurrentIsolateForSandbox();
837  os << " - embedder fields = {";
838  for (int i = 0; i < embedder_fields; i++) {
839  os << "\n ";
840  PrintEmbedderData(isolate, os, EmbedderDataSlot(obj, i));
841  }
842  os << "\n }\n";
843  }
844 }

869 void JSGeneratorObject::JSGeneratorObjectPrint(std::ostream& os) {
870  JSObjectPrintHeader(os, *this, "JSGeneratorObject");
871  os << "\n - function: " << Brief(function());
872  os << "\n - context: " << Brief(context());
873  os << "\n - receiver: " << Brief(receiver());
874  if (is_executing() || is_closed()) {
875  os << "\n - input: " << Brief(input_or_debug_pos());
876  } else {
877  DCHECK(is_suspended());
878  os << "\n - debug pos: " << Brief(input_or_debug_pos());
879  }
880  const char* mode = "(invalid)";
881  switch (resume_mode()) {
882  case kNext:
883  mode = ".next()";
884  break;
885  case kReturn:
886  mode = ".return()";
887  break;
888  case kThrow:
889  mode = ".throw()";
890  break;
891  }
892  os << "\n - resume mode: " << mode;
893  os << "\n - continuation: " << continuation();
894  if (is_closed()) os << " (closed)";
895  if (is_executing()) os << " (executing)";
896  if (is_suspended()) os << " (suspended)";
897  if (is_suspended()) {
898  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
899  Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> fun_info = function()->shared();
900  if (fun_info->HasSourceCode()) {
901  Tagged<Script> script = Cast<Script>(fun_info->script());
902  Tagged<String> script_name = IsString(script->name())
903  ? Cast<String>(script->name())
904  : GetReadOnlyRoots().empty_string();
905 
906  os << "\n - source position: ";
907  // Can't collect source positions here if not available as that would
908  // allocate memory.
909  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
910  if (fun_info->HasBytecodeArray() &&
911  fun_info->GetBytecodeArray(isolate)->HasSourcePositionTable()) {
912  os << source_position();
913  os << " (";
914  script_name->PrintUC16(os);
915  Script::PositionInfo info;
916  script->GetPositionInfo(source_position(), &info);
917  os << ", line " << info.line + 1;
918  os << ", column " << info.column + 1;
919  } else {
920  os << kUnavailableString;
921  }
922  os << ")";
923  }
924  }
925  os << "\n - register file: " << Brief(parameters_and_registers());
926  JSObjectPrintBody(os, *this);
927 }

1079 template <typename T>
1080 void PrintWeakArrayElements(std::ostream& os, T* array) {
1081  // Print in array notation for non-sparse arrays.
1082  Tagged<MaybeObject> previous_value =
1083  array->length() > 0 ? array->get(0) : Tagged<MaybeObject>(kNullAddress);
1084  Tagged<MaybeObject> value;
1085  int previous_index = 0;
1086  int i;
1087  for (i = 1; i <= array->length(); i++) {
1088  if (i < array->length()) value = array->get(i);
1089  if (previous_value == value && i != array->length()) {
1090  continue;
1091  }
1092  os << "\n";
1093  std::stringstream ss;
1094  ss << previous_index;
1095  if (previous_index != i - 1) {
1096  ss << '-' << (i - 1);
1097  }
1098  os << std::setw(12) << ss.str() << ": " << Brief(previous_value);
1099  previous_index = i;
1100  previous_value = value;
1101  }
1102 }

1388 namespace {
1389 using DataPrinter = std::function<void(InternalIndex)>;
1390 
1391 // Prints the data associated with each key (but no headers or other meta
1392 // data) in a hash table. Works on different hash table types, like the
1393 // subtypes of HashTable and OrderedHashTable. |print_data_at| is given an
1394 // index into the table (where a valid key resides) and prints the data at
1395 // that index, like just the value (in case of a hash map), or value and
1396 // property details (in case of a property dictionary). No leading space
1397 // required or trailing newline required. It can be null/non-callable
1398 // std::function to indicate that there is no associated data to be printed
1399 // (for example in case of a hash set).
1400 template <typename T>
1401 void PrintTableContentsGeneric(std::ostream& os, T* dict,
1402  DataPrinter print_data_at) {
1403  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1404  ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
1405 
1406  for (InternalIndex i : dict->IterateEntries()) {
1407  Tagged<Object> k;
1408  if (!dict->ToKey(roots, i, &k)) continue;
1409  os << "\n " << std::setw(12) << i.as_int() << ": ";
1410  if (IsString(k)) {
1411  Cast<String>(k)->PrintUC16(os);
1412  } else {
1413  os << Brief(k);
1414  }
1415  if (print_data_at) {
1416  os << " -> ";
1417  print_data_at(i);
1418  }
1419  }
1420 }
1421 
1422 void PrintNameDictionaryFlags(std::ostream& os, Tagged<NameDictionary> dict) {
1423  if (dict->may_have_interesting_properties()) {
1424  os << "\n - may_have_interesting_properties";
1425  }
1426 }
1427 
1428 // Used for ordered and unordered dictionaries.
1429 template <typename T>
1430 void PrintDictionaryContentsFull(std::ostream& os, T* dict) {
1431  os << "\n - elements: {";
1432  auto print_value_and_property_details = [&](InternalIndex i) {
1433  os << Brief(dict->ValueAt(i)) << " ";
1434  dict->DetailsAt(i).PrintAsSlowTo(os, !T::kIsOrderedDictionaryType);
1435  };
1436  PrintTableContentsGeneric(os, dict, print_value_and_property_details);
1437  os << "\n }\n";
1438 }
1439 
1440 // Used for ordered and unordered hash maps.
1441 template <typename T>
1442 void PrintHashMapContentsFull(std::ostream& os, T* dict) {
1443  os << "\n - elements: {";
1444  auto print_value = [&](InternalIndex i) { os << Brief(dict->ValueAt(i)); };
1445  PrintTableContentsGeneric(os, dict, print_value);
1446  os << "\n }\n";
1447 }
1448 
1449 // Used for ordered and unordered hash sets.
1450 template <typename T>
1451 void PrintHashSetContentsFull(std::ostream& os, T* dict) {
1452  os << "\n - elements: {";
1453  // Passing non-callable std::function as there are no values to print.
1454  PrintTableContentsGeneric(os, dict, nullptr);
1455  os << "\n }\n";
1456 }

1468  os << "\n - buckets: " << table->NumberOfBuckets();

1563 void SwissNameDictionary::SwissNameDictionaryPrint(std::ostream& os) {
1564  this->PrintHeader(os, "SwissNameDictionary");
1565  os << "\n - meta table ByteArray: "
1566  << reinterpret_cast<void*>(this->meta_table().ptr());
1567  os << "\n - capacity: " << this->Capacity();
1568  os << "\n - elements: " << this->NumberOfElements();
1569  os << "\n - deleted: " << this->NumberOfDeletedElements();
1570 
1571  std::ios_base::fmtflags sav_flags = os.flags();
1572  os << "\n - ctrl table (omitting buckets where key is hole value): {";
1573  for (int i = 0; i < this->Capacity() + kGroupWidth; i++) {
1574  ctrl_t ctrl = CtrlTable()[i];
1575 
1576  if (ctrl == Ctrl::kEmpty) continue;
1577 
1578  os << "\n " << std::setw(12) << std::dec << i << ": ";
1579  switch (ctrl) {
1580  case Ctrl::kEmpty:
1581  UNREACHABLE();
1582  case Ctrl::kDeleted:
1583  print_hex_byte(os, ctrl);
1584  os << " (= kDeleted)";
1585  break;
1586  case Ctrl::kSentinel:
1587  print_hex_byte(os, ctrl);
1588  os << " (= kSentinel)";
1589  break;
1590  default:
1591  print_hex_byte(os, ctrl);
1592  os << " (= H2 of a key)";
1593  break;
1594  }
1595  }
1596  os << "\n }";
1597 
1598  os << "\n - enumeration table: {";
1599  for (int enum_index = 0; enum_index < this->UsedCapacity(); enum_index++) {
1600  int entry = EntryForEnumerationIndex(enum_index);
1601  os << "\n " << std::setw(12) << std::dec << enum_index << ": " << entry;
1602  }
1603  os << "\n }";
1604 
1605  os << "\n - data table (omitting slots where key is the hole): {";
1606  for (int bucket = 0; bucket < this->Capacity(); ++bucket) {
1607  Tagged<Object> k;
1608  if (!this->ToKey(GetReadOnlyRoots(), bucket, &k)) continue;
1609 
1610  Tagged<Object> value = this->ValueAtRaw(bucket);
1611  PropertyDetails details = this->DetailsAt(bucket);
1612  os << "\n " << std::setw(12) << std::dec << bucket << ": ";
1613  if (IsString(k)) {
1614  Cast<String>(k)->PrintUC16(os);
1615  } else {
1616  os << Brief(k);
1617  }
1618  os << " -> " << Brief(value);
1619  details.PrintAsSlowTo(os, false);
1620  }
1621  os << "\n }\n";
1622  os.flags(sav_flags);
1623 }

1729 void FeedbackVectorSpec::FeedbackVectorSpecPrint(std::ostream& os) {
1730  os << " - slot_count: " << slot_count();
1731  if (slot_count() == 0) {
1732  os << " (empty)\n";
1733  return;
1734  }
1735 
1736  for (int slot = 0; slot < slot_count();) {
1737  FeedbackSlotKind kind = GetKind(FeedbackSlot(slot));
1738  int entry_size = FeedbackMetadata::GetSlotSize(kind);
1739  DCHECK_LT(0, entry_size);
1740  os << "\n Slot #" << slot << " " << kind;
1741  slot += entry_size;
1742  }
1743  os << "\n";
1744 }

1768 void FeedbackVector::FeedbackVectorPrint(std::ostream& os) {
1769  PrintHeader(os, "FeedbackVector");
1770  os << "\n - length: " << length();
1771  if (length() == 0) {
1772  os << " (empty)\n";
1773  return;
1774  }
1775 
1776  os << "\n - shared function info: " << Brief(shared_function_info());
1777 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1778  os << "\n - tiering_in_progress: " << tiering_in_progress();
1779 #else
1780  os << "\n - tiering state: " << tiering_state();
1781  if (has_optimized_code()) {
1782  os << "\n - optimized code: "
1783  << Brief(optimized_code(GetCurrentIsolateForSandbox()));
1784  } else {
1785  os << "\n - no optimized code";
1786  }
1787  os << "\n - maybe has maglev code: " << maybe_has_maglev_code();
1788  os << "\n - maybe has turbofan code: " << maybe_has_turbofan_code();
1789 #endif // !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1790  os << "\n - osr_tiering_in_progress: " << osr_tiering_in_progress();
1791  os << "\n - invocation count: " << invocation_count();
1792  os << "\n - closure feedback cell array: ";
1793  closure_feedback_cell_array()->ClosureFeedbackCellArrayPrint(os);
1794 
1795  FeedbackMetadataIterator iter(metadata());
1796  while (iter.HasNext()) {
1797  FeedbackSlot slot = iter.Next();
1798  FeedbackSlotKind kind = iter.kind();
1799 
1800  os << "\n - slot " << slot << " " << kind << " ";
1801  FeedbackSlotPrint(os, slot);
1802 
1803  int entry_size = iter.entry_size();
1804  if (entry_size > 0) os << " {";
1805  for (int i = 0; i < entry_size; i++) {
1806  FeedbackSlot slot_with_offset = slot.WithOffset(i);
1807  os << "\n [" << slot_with_offset.ToInt()
1808  << "]: " << Brief(Get(slot_with_offset));
1809  }
1810  if (entry_size > 0) os << "\n }";
1811  }
1812  os << "\n";
1813 }

1819 
1820 void FeedbackNexus::Print(std::ostream& os) {
1821  auto slot_kind = kind();
1822  switch (slot_kind) {
1823  case FeedbackSlotKind::kCall:
1824  case FeedbackSlotKind::kCloneObject:
1825  case FeedbackSlotKind::kHasKeyed:
1826  case FeedbackSlotKind::kInstanceOf:
1827  case FeedbackSlotKind::kTypeOf:
1828  case FeedbackSlotKind::kDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteral:
1829  case FeedbackSlotKind::kStoreInArrayLiteral: {
1830  os << InlineCacheState2String(ic_state());
1831  break;
1832  }
1833  case FeedbackSlotKind::kLoadGlobalInsideTypeof:
1834  case FeedbackSlotKind::kLoadGlobalNotInsideTypeof:
1835  case FeedbackSlotKind::kStoreGlobalSloppy:
1836  case FeedbackSlotKind::kStoreGlobalStrict: {
1837  os << InlineCacheState2String(ic_state());
1838  if (ic_state() == InlineCacheState::MONOMORPHIC) {
1839  os << "\n ";
1840  if (GetFeedback().IsCleared()) {
1841  // Handler mode: feedback is the cleared value, extra is the handler.
1842  if (IsLoadGlobalICKind(slot_kind)) {
1843  LoadHandler::PrintHandler(GetFeedbackExtra().GetHeapObjectOrSmi(),
1844  os);
1845  } else {
1846  StoreHandler::PrintHandler(GetFeedbackExtra().GetHeapObjectOrSmi(),
1847  os);
1848  }
1849  } else if (IsPropertyCell(GetFeedback().GetHeapObjectOrSmi())) {
1850  os << Brief(GetFeedback());
1851  } else {
1852  // Lexical variable mode: the variable location is encoded in the SMI.
1853  int handler = GetFeedback().GetHeapObjectOrSmi().ToSmi().value();
1854  os << (IsLoadGlobalICKind(slot_kind) ? "Load" : "Store");
1855  os << "Handler(Lexical variable mode)(context ix = "
1856  << FeedbackNexus::ContextIndexBits::decode(handler)
1857  << ", slot ix = " << FeedbackNexus::SlotIndexBits::decode(handler)
1858  << ")";
1859  }
1860  }
1861  break;
1862  }
1863  case FeedbackSlotKind::kLoadKeyed:
1864  case FeedbackSlotKind::kLoadProperty: {
1865  os << InlineCacheState2String(ic_state());
1866  if (ic_state() == InlineCacheState::MONOMORPHIC) {
1867  os << "\n " << Brief(GetFeedback()) << ": ";
1868  if (GetFeedbackExtra().IsCleared()) {
1869  os << " [cleared]\n";
1870  break;
1871  }
1872  Tagged<Object> handler = GetFeedbackExtra().GetHeapObjectOrSmi();
1873  if (IsWeakFixedArray(handler) &&
1874  !Cast<WeakFixedArray>(handler)->get(0).IsCleared()) {
1875  handler = Cast<WeakFixedArray>(handler)->get(0).GetHeapObjectOrSmi();
1876  }
1877  LoadHandler::PrintHandler(handler, os);
1878  } else if (ic_state() == InlineCacheState::POLYMORPHIC) {
1879  Tagged<HeapObject> feedback = GetFeedback().GetHeapObject();
1880  Tagged<WeakFixedArray> array;
1881  if (IsName(feedback)) {
1882  os << " with name " << Brief(feedback);
1883  array = Cast<WeakFixedArray>(GetFeedbackExtra().GetHeapObject());
1884  } else {
1885  array = Cast<WeakFixedArray>(feedback);
1886  }
1887  for (int i = 0; i < array->length(); i += 2) {
1888  os << "\n " << Brief(array->get(i)) << ": ";
1889  if (!array->get(i + 1).IsCleared()) {
1890  LoadHandler::PrintHandler(array->get(i + 1).GetHeapObjectOrSmi(),
1891  os);
1892  } else {
1893  os << "[cleared]\n";
1894  }
1895  }
1896  }
1897  break;
1898  }
1899  case FeedbackSlotKind::kDefineNamedOwn:
1900  case FeedbackSlotKind::kDefineKeyedOwn:
1901  case FeedbackSlotKind::kSetNamedSloppy:
1902  case FeedbackSlotKind::kSetNamedStrict:
1903  case FeedbackSlotKind::kSetKeyedSloppy:
1904  case FeedbackSlotKind::kSetKeyedStrict: {
1905  os << InlineCacheState2String(ic_state());
1906  if (GetFeedback().IsCleared()) {
1907  os << "\n [cleared]";
1908  break;
1909  }
1910  if (ic_state() == InlineCacheState::MONOMORPHIC) {
1911  Tagged<HeapObject> feedback = GetFeedback().GetHeapObject();
1912  if (GetFeedbackExtra().IsCleared()) {
1913  os << " [cleared]\n";
1914  break;
1915  }
1916  if (IsName(feedback)) {
1917  os << " with name " << Brief(feedback);
1918  Tagged<WeakFixedArray> array =
1919  Cast<WeakFixedArray>(GetFeedbackExtra().GetHeapObject());
1920  os << "\n " << Brief(array->get(0)) << ": ";
1921  if (array->get(1).IsCleared()) {
1922  os << "[cleared]\n";
1923  } else {
1924  Tagged<Object> handler = array->get(1).GetHeapObjectOrSmi();
1925  StoreHandler::PrintHandler(handler, os);
1926  }
1927  } else {
1928  os << "\n " << Brief(feedback) << ": ";
1929  StoreHandler::PrintHandler(GetFeedbackExtra().GetHeapObjectOrSmi(),
1930  os);
1931  }
1932  } else if (ic_state() == InlineCacheState::POLYMORPHIC) {
1933  Tagged<HeapObject> feedback = GetFeedback().GetHeapObject();
1934  Tagged<WeakFixedArray> array;
1935  if (IsName(feedback)) {
1936  os << " with name " << Brief(feedback);
1937  array = Cast<WeakFixedArray>(GetFeedbackExtra().GetHeapObject());
1938  } else {
1939  array = Cast<WeakFixedArray>(feedback);
1940  }
1941  for (int i = 0; i < array->length(); i += 2) {
1942  os << "\n " << Brief(array->get(i)) << ": ";
1943  if (!array->get(i + 1).IsCleared()) {
1944  StoreHandler::PrintHandler(array->get(i + 1).GetHeapObjectOrSmi(),
1945  os);
1946  }
1947  }
1948  }
1949  break;
1950  }
1951  case FeedbackSlotKind::kBinaryOp: {
1952  os << "BinaryOp:" << GetBinaryOperationFeedback();
1953  break;
1954  }
1955  case FeedbackSlotKind::kCompareOp: {
1956  os << "CompareOp:" << GetCompareOperationFeedback();
1957  break;
1958  }
1959  case FeedbackSlotKind::kForIn: {
1960  os << "ForIn:" << GetForInFeedback();
1961  break;
1962  }
1963  case FeedbackSlotKind::kLiteral:
1964  break;
1965  case FeedbackSlotKind::kJumpLoop:
1966  os << "JumpLoop";
1967  break;
1968  case FeedbackSlotKind::kStringAddAndInternalize: {
1969  os << "StringAddAndInternalize:" << GetBinaryOperationFeedback()
1970  << " with cache " << Brief(Cast<Object>(GetFeedbackExtra()));
1971  break;
1972  }
1973  case FeedbackSlotKind::kInvalid:
1974  UNREACHABLE();
1975  }
1976 }

2374 void JSFunction::JSFunctionPrint(std::ostream& os) {
2375  Isolate* isolate = Isolate::Current();
2376  JSObjectPrintHeader(os, *this, "Function");
2377  os << "\n - function prototype: ";
2378  if (has_prototype_slot()) {
2379  if (has_prototype()) {
2380  os << Brief(prototype());
2381  if (map()->has_non_instance_prototype()) {
2382  os << " (non-instance prototype)";
2383  }
2384  }
2385  os << "\n - initial_map: ";
2386  if (has_initial_map()) os << Brief(initial_map());
2387  } else {
2388  os << "<no-prototype-slot>";
2389  }
2390  os << "\n - shared_info: " << Brief(shared());
2391  os << "\n - name: " << Brief(shared()->Name());
2392 
2393  // Print Builtin name for builtin functions
2394  Builtin builtin = code(isolate)->builtin_id();
2395  if (Builtins::IsBuiltinId(builtin)) {
2396  os << "\n - builtin: " << isolate->builtins()->name(builtin);
2397  }
2398 
2399  os << "\n - formal_parameter_count: ";
2400  int formal_parameter_count =
2401  shared()->internal_formal_parameter_count_with_receiver();
2402  if (formal_parameter_count == kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel) {
2403  os << "kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel";
2404  } else {
2405  os << formal_parameter_count;
2406  }
2407  os << "\n - kind: " << shared()->kind();
2408  os << "\n - context: " << Brief(context());
2409  os << "\n - code: " << Brief(code(isolate));
2410 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
2411  os << "\n - dispatch_handle: 0x" << std::hex << dispatch_handle() << std::dec;
2412  if (has_feedback_vector() &&
2413  raw_feedback_cell()->dispatch_handle() != dispatch_handle()) {
2414  os << "\n - canonical feedback cell dispatch_handle: 0x" << std::hex
2415  << raw_feedback_cell()->dispatch_handle() << std::dec;
2416  }
2417  if (IsTieringRequestedOrInProgress()) {
2418  os << "\n - tiering request ";
2419  if (tiering_in_progress()) {
2420  os << "in_progress ";
2421  }
2422  IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table()->PrintCurrentTieringRequest(
2423  dispatch_handle(), Isolate::Current(), os);
2424  }
2425 
2426 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
2427  if (code(isolate)->kind() == CodeKind::FOR_TESTING) {
2428  os << "\n - FOR_TESTING";
2429  } else if (ActiveTierIsIgnition(isolate)) {
2430  os << "\n - interpreted";
2431  if (shared()->HasBytecodeArray()) {
2432  os << "\n - bytecode: " << shared()->GetBytecodeArray(isolate);
2433  }
2434  }
2435 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2436  if (WasmExportedFunction::IsWasmExportedFunction(*this)) {
2437  Tagged<WasmExportedFunction> function = Cast<WasmExportedFunction>(*this);
2438  Tagged<WasmExportedFunctionData> data =
2439  function->shared()->wasm_exported_function_data();
2440  os << "\n - Wasm instance data: " << Brief(data->instance_data());
2441  os << "\n - Wasm function index: " << data->function_index();
2442  }
2443  if (WasmJSFunction::IsWasmJSFunction(*this)) {
2444  Tagged<WasmJSFunction> function = Cast<WasmJSFunction>(*this);
2445  os << "\n - Wasm wrapper around: "
2446  << Brief(function->shared()->wasm_js_function_data()->GetCallable());
2447  }
2448 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2449  shared()->PrintSourceCode(os);
2450  JSObjectPrintBody(os, *this);
2451  os << " - feedback vector: ";
2452  if (!shared()->HasFeedbackMetadata()) {
2453  os << "feedback metadata is not available in SFI\n";
2454  } else if (has_feedback_vector()) {
2455  feedback_vector()->FeedbackVectorPrint(os);
2456  } else if (has_closure_feedback_cell_array()) {
2457  os << "No feedback vector, but we have a closure feedback cell array\n";
2458  closure_feedback_cell_array()->ClosureFeedbackCellArrayPrint(os);
2459  } else {
2460  os << "not available\n";
2461  }
2462 }

2579 void Code::CodePrint(std::ostream& os, const char* name, Address current_pc) {

2592  os << "\n - instruction_stream: " << Brief(raw_instruction_stream());
2593  os << "\n - instruction_start: "
2594  << reinterpret_cast<void*>(instruction_start());

2598  os << "\n - embedded_objects_cleared: " << embedded_objects_cleared();
2599  os << "\n - can_have_weak_objects: " << can_have_weak_objects();
2600  os << "\n - instruction_size: " << instruction_size();
2601  os << "\n - metadata_size: " << metadata_size();
2602 
2603  if (kind() != CodeKind::WASM_TO_JS_FUNCTION) {
2604  os << "\n - inlined_bytecode_size: " << inlined_bytecode_size();
2605  } else {
2606  os << "\n - wasm_js_tagged_parameter_count: "

2611  os << "\n - osr_offset: " << osr_offset();
2612  os << "\n - handler_table_offset: " << handler_table_offset();
2613  os << "\n - unwinding_info_offset: " << unwinding_info_offset();

2615  os << "\n - constant_pool_offset: " << constant_pool_offset();
2616  }
2617  os << "\n - code_comments_offset: " << code_comments_offset();
2618 
2619  // Then, InstructionStream:
2620  if (has_instruction_stream()) {
2621  Tagged<InstructionStream> istream = instruction_stream();
2622  os << "\n - instruction_stream.relocation_info: "

2626 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
2627  os << "\n - dispatch_handle: 0x" << std::hex << js_dispatch_handle()
2628  << std::dec;
2629 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
2630  os << "\n";
2631 
2632  // Finally, the disassembly:
2633 #ifdef ENABLE_DISASSEMBLER
2634  os << "\n--- Disassembly: ---\n";
2635  Disassemble(name, os, Isolate::Current(), current_pc);
2636 #endif
2637 }

2757 void WasmStruct::WasmStructPrint(std::ostream& os) {
2758  PrintHeader(os, "WasmStruct");
2759  const wasm::CanonicalStructType* struct_type =
2760  wasm::GetTypeCanonicalizer()->LookupStruct(
2761  map()->wasm_type_info()->type_index());
2762  if (struct_type->is_descriptor()) {
2763  os << "\n - describes RTT: " << Brief(described_rtt());
2764  }
2765  os << "\n - fields (" << struct_type->field_count() << "):";
2766  for (uint32_t i = 0; i < struct_type->field_count(); i++) {
2767  wasm::CanonicalValueType field = struct_type->field(i);
2768  os << "\n - " << field.short_name() << ": ";
2769  uint32_t field_offset = struct_type->field_offset(i);
2770  Address field_address = RawFieldAddress(field_offset);
2771  switch (field.kind()) {
2772  case wasm::kI32:
2773  os << base::ReadUnalignedValue<int32_t>(field_address);
2774  break;
2775  case wasm::kI64:
2776  os << base::ReadUnalignedValue<int64_t>(field_address);
2777  break;
2778  case wasm::kF16:
2779  os << fp16_ieee_to_fp32_value(
2780  base::ReadUnalignedValue<uint16_t>(field_address));
2781  break;
2782  case wasm::kF32:
2783  os << base::ReadUnalignedValue<float>(field_address);
2784  break;
2785  case wasm::kF64:
2786  os << base::ReadUnalignedValue<double>(field_address);
2787  break;
2788  case wasm::kI8:
2789  os << base::ReadUnalignedValue<int8_t>(field_address);
2790  break;
2791  case wasm::kI16:
2792  os << base::ReadUnalignedValue<int16_t>(field_address);
2793  break;
2794  case wasm::kRef:
2795  case wasm::kRefNull: {
2796  Tagged_t raw = base::ReadUnalignedValue<Tagged_t>(field_address);
2797 #if V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
2798  Address obj = V8HeapCompressionScheme::DecompressTagged(raw);
2799 #else
2800  Address obj = raw;
2801 #endif
2802  os << Brief(Tagged<Object>(obj));
2803  break;
2804  }
2805  case wasm::kS128:
2806  os << "0x" << std::hex << std::setfill('0');
2807 #ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
2808  for (int j = 0; j < kSimd128Size; j++) {
2809 #else
2810  for (int j = kSimd128Size - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
2811 #endif
2812  os << std::setw(2)
2813  << static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(field_address)[j]);
2814  }
2815  os << std::dec << std::setfill(' ');
2816  break;
2817  case wasm::kTop:
2818  case wasm::kBottom:
2819  case wasm::kVoid:
2820  UNREACHABLE();
2821  }
2822  }
2823  os << "\n";
2824 }

2826 void WasmArray::WasmArrayPrint(std::ostream& os) {

2829  map()->wasm_type_info()->element_type();
2830  uint32_t len = length();
2831  os << "\n - element type: " << element_type.name();
2832  os << "\n - length: " << len;
2833  Address data_ptr = ptr() + WasmArray::kHeaderSize - kHeapObjectTag;
2834  switch (element_type.kind()) {
2835  case wasm::kI32:
2836  PrintTypedArrayElements(os, reinterpret_cast<int32_t*>(data_ptr), len,
2837  true);
2838  break;
2839  case wasm::kI64:
2840  PrintTypedArrayElements(os, reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(data_ptr), len,
2841  true);
2842  break;
2843  case wasm::kF16:
2844  PrintTypedArrayElements(os, reinterpret_cast<Fp16Printer*>(data_ptr), len,
2845  true);
2846  break;
2847  case wasm::kF32:
2848  PrintTypedArrayElements(os, reinterpret_cast<float*>(data_ptr), len,
2849  true);
2850  break;
2851  case wasm::kF64:
2852  PrintTypedArrayElements(os, reinterpret_cast<double*>(data_ptr), len,
2853  true);
2854  break;
2855  case wasm::kI8:
2856  PrintTypedArrayElements(os, reinterpret_cast<int8_t*>(data_ptr), len,
2857  true);
2858  break;
2859  case wasm::kI16:
2860  PrintTypedArrayElements(os, reinterpret_cast<int16_t*>(data_ptr), len,
2861  true);
2862  break;
2863  case wasm::kRef:
2864  case wasm::kRefNull: {
2865  os << "\n - elements:";
2866  constexpr uint32_t kWasmArrayMaximumPrintedElements = 5;
2867  for (uint32_t i = 0;
2868  i < std::min(this->length(), kWasmArrayMaximumPrintedElements);
2869  i++) {
2870  os << "\n " << static_cast<int>(i) << " - "
2871  << Brief(TaggedField<Object>::load(*this, this->element_offset(i)));
2872  }
2873  if (this->length() > kWasmArrayMaximumPrintedElements) os << "\n ...";
2874  break;
2875  }
2876  case wasm::kS128: {
2877  os << "\n - elements:";
2878  constexpr uint32_t kWasmArrayMaximumPrintedElements = 5;
2879  for (uint32_t i = 0;
2880  i < std::min(this->length(), kWasmArrayMaximumPrintedElements);
2881  i++) {
2882  os << "\n " << static_cast<int>(i) << " - 0x" << std::hex
2883  << std::setfill('0');
2884 #ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
2885  for (int j = 0; j < kSimd128Size; j++) {
2886 #else
2887  for (int j = kSimd128Size - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
2888 #endif
2889  os << std::setw(2)
2890  << static_cast<int>(
2891  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this->ElementAddress(i))[j]);
2892  }
2893  os << std::dec << std::setfill(' ');
2894  }
2895  if (this->length() > kWasmArrayMaximumPrintedElements) os << "\n ...";
2896  break;
2897  }
2898  case wasm::kTop:
2899  case wasm::kBottom:
2900  case wasm::kVoid:
2901  UNREACHABLE();
2902  }
2903  os << "\n";
2904 }

3432 namespace {
3433 void PrintScopeInfoList(Tagged<ScopeInfo> scope_info, std::ostream& os,
3434  const char* list_name, int length) {
3435  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3436  if (length <= 0) return;
3437  os << "\n - " << list_name;
3438  os << " {\n";
3439  for (auto it : ScopeInfo::IterateLocalNames(scope_info, no_gc)) {
3440  os << " - " << it->index() << ": " << it->name() << "\n";
3441  }
3442  os << " }";
3443 }

3446 void ScopeInfo::ScopeInfoPrint(std::ostream& os) {
3447  PrintHeader(os, "ScopeInfo");
3448  if (this->IsEmpty()) {
3449  os << "\n - empty\n";
3450  return;
3451  }
3452  int flags = Flags();
3453 
3454  os << "\n - parameters: " << ParameterCount();
3455  os << "\n - context locals : " << ContextLocalCount();
3456  if (HasInlinedLocalNames()) {
3457  os << "\n - inlined local names";
3458  } else {
3459  os << "\n - local names in a hashtable: "
3460  << Brief(context_local_names_hashtable());
3461  }
3462 
3463  os << "\n - scope type: " << scope_type();
3464  if (SloppyEvalCanExtendVars()) {
3465  os << "\n - sloppy eval";
3466  os << "\n - dependent code: " << Brief(dependent_code());
3467  }
3468  os << "\n - language mode: " << language_mode();
3469  if (is_declaration_scope()) os << "\n - declaration scope";
3470  if (HasReceiver()) {
3471  os << "\n - receiver: " << ReceiverVariableBits::decode(flags);
3472  }
3473  if (ClassScopeHasPrivateBrand()) os << "\n - class scope has private brand";
3474  if (HasSavedClassVariable()) os << "\n - has saved class variable";
3475  if (HasNewTarget()) os << "\n - needs new target";
3476  if (HasFunctionName()) {
3477  os << "\n - function name(" << FunctionVariableBits::decode(flags) << "): ";
3478  ShortPrint(FunctionName(), os);
3479  }
3480  if (IsAsmModule()) os << "\n - asm module";
3481  if (HasSimpleParameters()) os << "\n - simple parameters";
3482  if (PrivateNameLookupSkipsOuterClass())
3483  os << "\n - private name lookup skips outer class";
3484  os << "\n - function kind: " << function_kind();
3485  if (HasOuterScopeInfo()) {
3486  os << "\n - outer scope info: " << Brief(OuterScopeInfo());
3487  }
3488  if (HasFunctionName()) {
3489  os << "\n - function name: " << Brief(FunctionName());
3490  }
3491  if (HasInferredFunctionName()) {
3492  os << "\n - inferred function name: " << Brief(InferredFunctionName());
3493  }
3494  if (HasContextExtensionSlot()) {
3495  os << "\n - has context extension slot";
3496  }
3497 
3498  if (HasPositionInfo()) {
3499  os << "\n - start position: " << StartPosition();
3500  os << "\n - end position: " << EndPosition();
3501  }
3502  os << "\n - length: " << length();
3503  if (length() > 0) {
3504  PrintScopeInfoList(*this, os, "context slots", ContextLocalCount());
3505  // TODO(neis): Print module stuff if present.
3506  }
3507  os << "\n";
3508 }

3545 void HeapObject::HeapObjectShortPrint(std::ostream& os) {
3546  PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase();
3547  os << AsHex::Address(this->ptr()) << " ";
3548 
3549  if (IsString(*this, cage_base)) {
3550  HeapStringAllocator allocator;
3551  StringStream accumulator(&allocator);
3552  Cast<String>(*this)->StringShortPrint(&accumulator);
3553  os << accumulator.ToCString().get();
3554  return;
3555  }
3556  if (IsJSObject(*this, cage_base)) {
3557  HeapStringAllocator allocator;
3558  StringStream accumulator(&allocator);
3559  Cast<JSObject>(*this)->JSObjectShortPrint(&accumulator);
3560  os << accumulator.ToCString().get();
3561  return;
3562  }
3563 
3564  InstanceType instance_type = map(cage_base)->instance_type();
3565 
3566  // Skip invalid trusted objects. Technically it'd be fine to still handle
3567  // them below since we only print the objects, but such an object will
3568  // quickly lead to out-of-sandbox segfaults and so fuzzers will complain.
3569  if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsTrustedObject(instance_type) &&
3570  !OutsideSandboxOrInReadonlySpace(*this)) {
3571  os << "<Invalid TrustedObject (outside trusted space)>\n";
3572  return;
3573  }
3574 
3575  switch (instance_type) {
3576  case MAP_TYPE: {
3577  Tagged<Map> map = Cast<Map>(*this);
3578  if (map->instance_type() == MAP_TYPE) {
3579  // This is one of the meta maps, print only relevant fields.
3580  os << "<MetaMap (" << Brief(map->native_context_or_null()) << ")>";
3581  } else {
3582  os << "<Map";
3583  if (map->instance_size() != kVariableSizeSentinel) {
3584  os << "[" << map->instance_size() << "]";
3585  }
3586  os << "(";
3587  if (IsJSObjectMap(map)) {
3588  os << ElementsKindToString(map->elements_kind());
3589  } else {
3590  os << map->instance_type();
3591  }
3592  os << ")>";
3593  }
3594  } break;
3595  case AWAIT_CONTEXT_TYPE: {
3596  os << "<AwaitContext generator= ";
3597  HeapStringAllocator allocator;
3598  StringStream accumulator(&allocator);
3599  ShortPrint(Cast<Context>(*this)->extension(), &accumulator);
3600  os << accumulator.ToCString().get();
3601  os << '>';
3602  break;
3603  }
3604  case BLOCK_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3605  os << "<BlockContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3606  break;
3607  case CATCH_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3608  os << "<CatchContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3609  break;
3610  case DEBUG_EVALUATE_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3611  os << "<DebugEvaluateContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3612  break;
3613  case EVAL_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3614  os << "<EvalContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3615  break;
3616  case FUNCTION_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3617  os << "<FunctionContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3618  break;
3619  case MODULE_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3620  os << "<ModuleContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3621  break;
3622  case NATIVE_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3623  os << "<NativeContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3624  break;
3625  case SCRIPT_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3626  os << "<ScriptContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3627  break;
3628  case WITH_CONTEXT_TYPE:
3629  os << "<WithContext[" << Cast<Context>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3630  break;
3631  case SCRIPT_CONTEXT_TABLE_TYPE:
3632  os << "<ScriptContextTable["
3633  << Cast<ScriptContextTable>(*this)->capacity() << "]>";
3634  break;
3635  case HASH_TABLE_TYPE:
3636  os << "<HashTable[" << Cast<FixedArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3637  break;
3638  case ORDERED_HASH_MAP_TYPE:
3639  os << "<OrderedHashMap[" << Cast<FixedArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3640  break;
3641  case ORDERED_HASH_SET_TYPE:
3642  os << "<OrderedHashSet[" << Cast<FixedArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3643  break;

3645  os << "<OrderedNameDictionary[" << Cast<FixedArray>(*this)->length()
3646  << "]>";

3649  os << "<NameDictionary[" << Cast<FixedArray>(*this)->length() << "]>";
3650  break;

3797 #define MAKE_STRUCT_CASE(TYPE, Name, name) \

3800  Cast<Name>(*this)->BriefPrintDetails(os); \
3801  os << ">"; \
3802  break;

3819  if (code->is_builtin()) {
3820  os << " " << Builtins::name(code->builtin_id());
3821  }
3822  os << ">";
3823  break;
3824  }
3825  case HOLE_TYPE: {
3826 #define PRINT_HOLE(Type, Value, _) \
3827  if (Is##Type(*this)) { \
3828  os << "<" #Value ">"; \
3829  break; \
3830  }
3831  HOLE_LIST(PRINT_HOLE)
3832 #undef PRINT_HOLE
3833  UNREACHABLE();
3834  }
3835  case INSTRUCTION_STREAM_TYPE: {

3837  Tagged<Code> code = istream->code(kAcquireLoad);
3838  os << "<InstructionStream " << CodeKindToString(code->kind());
3839  if (code->is_builtin()) {
3840  os << " " << Builtins::name(code->builtin_id());
3841  }
3842  os << ">";
3843  break;
3844  }
3845  case ODDBALL_TYPE: {
3846  if (IsUndefined(*this)) {
3847  os << "<undefined>";
3848  } else if (IsNull(*this)) {
3849  os << "<null>";
3850  } else if (IsTrue(*this)) {
3851  os << "<true>";
3852  } else if (IsFalse(*this)) {
3853  os << "<false>";
3854  } else {
3855  os << "<Odd Oddball: ";
3856  os << Cast<Oddball>(*this)->to_string()->ToCString().get();
3857  os << ">";
3858  }
3859  break;
3860  }
3861  case SYMBOL_TYPE: {

3864  break;
3865  }
3866  case HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE: {

3869  os << ">";
3870  break;

3876  break;
3877  }
3878  case JS_PROXY_TYPE:
3879  os << "<JSProxy>";
3880  break;
3881  case FOREIGN_TYPE:
3882  os << "<Foreign>";
3883  break;
3884  case CELL_TYPE: {
3885  os << "<Cell value= ";
3886  HeapStringAllocator allocator;
3887  StringStream accumulator(&allocator);
3888  ShortPrint(Cast<Cell>(*this)->value(), &accumulator);
3889  os << accumulator.ToCString().get();
3890  os << '>';
3891  break;
3892  }
3893  case PROPERTY_CELL_TYPE: {
3894  Tagged<PropertyCell> cell = Cast<PropertyCell>(*this);
3895  os << "<PropertyCell name=";
3896  ShortPrint(cell->name(), os);
3897  os << " value=";
3898  HeapStringAllocator allocator;
3899  StringStream accumulator(&allocator);
3900  ShortPrint(cell->value(kAcquireLoad), &accumulator);
3901  os << accumulator.ToCString().get();
3902  os << '>';
3903  break;
3904  }
3905  case ACCESSOR_INFO_TYPE: {
3906  Tagged<AccessorInfo> info = Cast<AccessorInfo>(*this);
3907  os << "<AccessorInfo ";
3908  os << "name= " << Brief(info->name());
3909  os << ", data= " << Brief(info->data());
3910  os << ">";
3911  break;
3912  }
3913  case FUNCTION_TEMPLATE_INFO_TYPE: {
3914  Tagged<FunctionTemplateInfo> info = Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(*this);
3915  os << "<FunctionTemplateInfo ";
3916  Isolate* isolate;
3917  if (GetIsolateFromHeapObject(*this, &isolate)) {
3918  os << "callback= " << reinterpret_cast<void*>(info->callback(isolate));
3919  } else {
3920  os << "callback= " << kUnavailableString;
3921  }
3922  os << ", data= " << Brief(info->callback_data(kAcquireLoad));
3923  os << ", has_side_effects= ";
3924  if (info->has_side_effects()) {
3925  os << "true>";
3926  } else {
3927  os << "false>";
3928  }
3929  break;
3930  }
3931 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3932  case WASM_DISPATCH_TABLE_TYPE:
3933  os << "<WasmDispatchTable[" << Cast<WasmDispatchTable>(*this)->length()
3934  << "]>";
3935  break;
3936 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3937  default:
3938  os << "<Other heap object (" << map()->instance_type() << ")>";
3939  break;
3940  }
3941 }

3996 void Map::MapPrint(std::ostream& os) {
3997  bool is_meta_map = instance_type() == MAP_TYPE;
3998 #ifdef OBJECT_PRINT
3999  PrintHeader(os, is_meta_map ? "MetaMap" : "Map");
4000 #else
4001  os << (is_meta_map ? "MetaMap=" : "Map=") << reinterpret_cast<void*>(ptr());
4002 #endif
4003  os << "\n - type: " << instance_type();
4004  os << "\n - instance size: ";
4005  if (instance_size() == kVariableSizeSentinel) {
4006  os << "variable";
4007  } else {
4008  os << instance_size();
4009  }
4010  if (is_meta_map) {
4011  // This is one of the meta maps, print only relevant fields.
4012  os << "\n - native_context: " << Brief(native_context_or_null());
4013  os << "\n";
4014  return;
4015  }
4016 
4017  if (IsJSObjectMap(*this)) {
4018  os << "\n - inobject properties: " << GetInObjectProperties();
4019  os << "\n - unused property fields: " << UnusedPropertyFields();
4020  }
4021  os << "\n - elements kind: " << ElementsKindToString(elements_kind());
4022  os << "\n - enum length: ";
4023  if (EnumLength() == kInvalidEnumCacheSentinel) {
4024  os << "invalid";
4025  } else {
4026  os << EnumLength();
4027  }
4028  if (is_deprecated()) os << "\n - deprecated_map";
4029  if (is_stable()) os << "\n - stable_map";
4030  if (is_migration_target()) os << "\n - migration_target";
4031  if (is_dictionary_map()) os << "\n - dictionary_map";
4032  if (has_named_interceptor()) os << "\n - named_interceptor";
4033  if (has_indexed_interceptor()) os << "\n - indexed_interceptor";
4034  if (may_have_interesting_properties())
4035  os << "\n - may_have_interesting_properties";
4036  if (is_undetectable()) os << "\n - undetectable";
4037  if (is_callable()) os << "\n - callable";
4038  if (is_constructor()) os << "\n - constructor";
4039  if (has_prototype_slot()) {
4040  os << "\n - has_prototype_slot";
4041  if (has_non_instance_prototype()) os << " (non-instance prototype)";
4042  }
4043  if (is_access_check_needed()) os << "\n - access_check_needed";
4044  if (!is_extensible()) os << "\n - non-extensible";
4045  if (IsContextMap(*this)) {
4046  os << "\n - native context: " << Brief(native_context());
4047  } else if (is_prototype_map()) {
4048  os << "\n - prototype_map";
4049  os << "\n - prototype info: " << Brief(prototype_info());
4050  } else {
4051  os << "\n - back pointer: " << Brief(GetBackPointer());
4052  }
4053  os << "\n - prototype_validity cell: "
4054  << Brief(prototype_validity_cell(kRelaxedLoad));
4055  os << "\n - instance descriptors " << (owns_descriptors() ? "(own) " : "")
4056  << "#" << NumberOfOwnDescriptors() << ": "
4057  << Brief(instance_descriptors());
4058 
4059  // Read-only maps can't have transitions, which is fortunate because we need
4060  // the isolate to iterate over the transitions.
4061  if (!HeapLayout::InReadOnlySpace(*this)) {
4062  Isolate* isolate = HeapLayout::InWritableSharedSpace(*this)
4063  ? Isolate::Current()->shared_space_isolate()
4064  : GetIsolateFromWritableObject(*this);
4065  TransitionsAccessor transitions(isolate, *this);
4066  int nof_transitions = transitions.NumberOfTransitions();
4067  if (nof_transitions > 0 || transitions.HasPrototypeTransitions() ||
4068  transitions.HasSideStepTransitions()) {
4069  os << "\n - transitions #" << nof_transitions << ": ";
4070  Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object;
4071  Tagged<Smi> smi;
4072  if (raw_transitions().ToSmi(&smi)) {
4073  os << Brief(smi);
4074  } else if (raw_transitions().GetHeapObject(&heap_object)) {
4075  os << Brief(heap_object);
4076  }
4077 #ifdef OBJECT_PRINT
4078  transitions.PrintTransitions(os);
4079 #endif // OBJECT_PRINT
4080  }
4081  }
4082  os << "\n - prototype: " << Brief(prototype());
4083  if (has_non_instance_prototype()) {
4084  os << "\n - non-instance prototype: " << Brief(GetNonInstancePrototype());
4085  }
4086  if (!IsContextMap(*this)) {
4087  os << "\n - constructor: " << Brief(GetConstructor());
4088  }
4089  os << "\n - dependent code: " << Brief(dependent_code());
4090  os << "\n - construction counter: " << construction_counter();
4091  os << "\n";
4092 }

4109 void DescriptorArray::PrintDescriptorDetails(std::ostream& os,

4134 // This method is only meant to be called from gdb for debugging purposes.
4135 // Since the string can also be in two-byte encoding, non-Latin1 characters
4136 // will be ignored in the output.
4137 char* String::ToAsciiArray() {
4138  // Static so that subsequent calls frees previously allocated space.
4139  // This also means that previous results will be overwritten.
4140  static char* buffer = nullptr;
4141  if (buffer != nullptr) delete[] buffer;
4142  buffer = new char[length() + 1];
4143  WriteToFlat(this, reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(buffer), 0, length());
4144  buffer[length()] = 0;
4145  return buffer;
4146 }

4149 void TransitionsAccessor::PrintOneTransition(std::ostream& os, Tagged<Name> key,
4150  Tagged<Map> target) {
4151  os << "\n ";
4152 #ifdef OBJECT_PRINT
4153  key->NamePrint(os);
4154 #else
4155  ShortPrint(key, os);
4156 #endif
4157  os << ": ";
4158  ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
4159  if (key == roots.nonextensible_symbol()) {
4160  os << "(transition to non-extensible)";
4161  } else if (key == roots.sealed_symbol()) {
4162  os << "(transition to sealed)";
4163  } else if (key == roots.frozen_symbol()) {
4164  os << "(transition to frozen)";
4165  } else if (key == roots.elements_transition_symbol()) {
4166  os << "(transition to " << ElementsKindToString(target->elements_kind())
4167  << ")";
4168  } else if (key == roots.strict_function_transition_symbol()) {
4169  os << " (transition to strict function)";
4170  } else {
4171  DCHECK(!IsSpecialTransition(roots, key));
4172  os << "(transition to ";
4173  InternalIndex descriptor = target->LastAdded();
4174  Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors = target->instance_descriptors();
4175  descriptors->PrintDescriptorDetails(os, descriptor,
4176  PropertyDetails::kForTransitions);
4177  os << ")";
4178  }
4179  os << " -> " << Brief(target);
4180 }

4182 void TransitionArray::PrintInternal(std::ostream& os) {
4183  {
4184  int num_transitions = number_of_transitions();
4185  os << "\n Transitions #" << num_transitions << ":";
4186  for (int i = 0; i < num_transitions; i++) {
4187  Tagged<Name> key = GetKey(i);
4188  Tagged<Map> target;
4189  GetTargetIfExists(i, GetIsolateFromWritableObject(*this), &target);
4190  TransitionsAccessor::PrintOneTransition(os, key, target);
4191  }
4192  }
4193 
4194  if (HasPrototypeTransitions()) {
4195  auto prototype_transitions = GetPrototypeTransitions();
4196  int num_transitions = NumberOfPrototypeTransitions(prototype_transitions);
4197  os << "\n Prototype transitions #" << num_transitions << ": "
4198  << Brief(prototype_transitions);
4199  for (int i = 0; i < num_transitions; i++) {
4200  auto maybe = prototype_transitions->get(
4201  TransitionArray::kProtoTransitionHeaderSize + i);
4202  Tagged<HeapObject> target;
4203  if (maybe.GetHeapObjectIfWeak(&target)) {
4204  auto map = Cast<Map>(target);
4205  os << "\n " << Brief(map->prototype()) << " -> "
4206  << Brief(Cast<Map>(target));
4207  }
4208  }
4209  }
4210 
4211  if (HasSideStepTransitions()) {
4212  auto sidestep_transitions = GetSideStepTransitions();
4213  int num_transitions = sidestep_transitions->length();
4214  os << "\n Sidestep transitions #" << num_transitions << ": "
4215  << Brief(sidestep_transitions);
4216  for (int i = 0; i < num_transitions; i++) {
4217  SideStepTransition::Kind kind = static_cast<SideStepTransition::Kind>(i);
4218  auto maybe_target = sidestep_transitions->get(i);
4219  os << "\n " << kind << " -> " << Brief(maybe_target);
4220  }
4221  }
4222 }

4224 void TransitionsAccessor::PrintTransitions(std::ostream& os) {
4225  switch (encoding()) {
4226  case kPrototypeInfo:
4227  case kUninitialized:
4228  case kMigrationTarget:
4229  return;
4230  case kWeakRef: {
4231  Tagged<Map> target =
4232  Cast<Map>(raw_transitions_.GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak());
4233  Tagged<Name> key = GetSimpleTransitionKey(target);
4234  PrintOneTransition(os, key, target);
4235  break;
4236  }
4237  case kFullTransitionArray:
4238  return transitions()->PrintInternal(os);
4239  }
4240 }

4251 void TransitionsAccessor::PrintTransitionTree(
4252  std::ostream& os, int level, DisallowGarbageCollection* no_gc) {
4253  ReadOnlyRoots roots = ReadOnlyRoots(isolate_);
4254  int pos = 0;
4255  int proto_pos = 0;
4256  ForEachTransitionWithKey(
4257  no_gc,
4258  [&](Tagged<Name> key, Tagged<Map> target) {
4259  os << std::endl
4260  << " " << level << "/" << pos << ":" << std::setw(level * 2 + 2)
4261  << " ";
4262  pos++;
4263  std::stringstream ss;
4264  ss << Brief(target);
4265  os << std::left << std::setw(50) << ss.str() << ": ";
4266 
4267  if (key == roots.nonextensible_symbol()) {
4268  os << "to non-extensible";
4269  } else if (key == roots.sealed_symbol()) {
4270  os << "to sealed ";
4271  } else if (key == roots.frozen_symbol()) {
4272  os << "to frozen";
4273  } else if (key == roots.elements_transition_symbol()) {
4274  os << "to " << ElementsKindToString(target->elements_kind());
4275  } else if (key == roots.strict_function_transition_symbol()) {
4276  os << "to strict function";
4277  } else {
4278 #ifdef OBJECT_PRINT
4279  key->NamePrint(os);
4280 #else
4281  ShortPrint(key, os);
4282 #endif
4283  os << " ";
4284  DCHECK(!IsSpecialTransition(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate_), key));
4285  os << "to ";
4286  InternalIndex descriptor = target->LastAdded();
4287  Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors =
4288  target->instance_descriptors(isolate_);
4289  descriptors->PrintDescriptorDetails(os, descriptor,
4290  PropertyDetails::kForTransitions);
4291  }
4292  TransitionsAccessor transitions(isolate_, target);
4293  transitions.PrintTransitionTree(os, level + 1, no_gc);
4294  },
4295  [&](Tagged<Map> target) {
4296  os << std::endl
4297  << " " << level << "/p" << proto_pos << ":"
4298  << std::setw(level * 2 + 2) << " ";
4299  proto_pos++;
4300  std::stringstream ss;
4301  ss << Brief(target);
4302  os << std::left << std::setw(50) << ss.str() << ": to proto ";
4303  ShortPrint(target->prototype(), os);
4304  TransitionsAccessor transitions(isolate_, target);
4305  transitions.PrintTransitionTree(os, level + 1, no_gc);
4306  },
4307  [&](SideStepTransition::Kind kind, Tagged<Object> side_step) {
4308  os << std::endl
4309  << " " << level << "/s:" << std::setw(level * 2 + 2) << " ";
4310  std::stringstream ss;
4311  ss << Brief(side_step);
4312  os << std::left << std::setw(50) << ss.str() << ": sidestep " << kind;
4313  });
4314 }

4329 inline i::Tagged<i::Object> GetObjectFromRaw(void* object) {
4330  i::Address object_ptr = reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(object);
4331 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
4332  if (RoundDown<i::kPtrComprCageBaseAlignment>(object_ptr) == i::kNullAddress) {
4333  // Try to decompress pointer.
4334  i::Isolate* isolate = i::Isolate::TryGetCurrent();
4335  if (isolate != nullptr) {
4336  object_ptr = i::V8HeapCompressionScheme::DecompressTagged(
4337  static_cast<i::Tagged_t>(object_ptr));
4338  } else {
4339  object_ptr = i::V8HeapCompressionScheme::DecompressTagged(
4340  static_cast<i::Tagged_t>(object_ptr));
4341  }
4342  }
4343 #endif
4344  return i::Tagged<i::Object>(object_ptr);
4345 }

4357 // Defines _As_XXX functions which are useful for inspecting object properties
4358 // in debugger:
4359 //
4360 // (gdb) p _As_ScopeInfo(0xead)->IsEmpty()
4361 // $1 = 0x1
4362 // (gdb) p _As_ScopeInfo(0x0e830009d555)->scope_type()
4363 // $2 = v8::internal::FUNCTION_SCOPE
4364 // (gdb) p _As_Undefined(0x11)->kind()
4365 // $3 = 0x4
4366 // (gdb) job _As_Oddball(0x2d)->to_string()
4367 // 0xe8300005309: [String] in ReadOnlySpace: #null
4368 //
4369 #define AS_HELPER_DEF(Type, ...) \
4370  V8_DEBUGGING_EXPORT auto& _As_##Type(i::Address ptr) { \
4371  i::Tagged<i::Type> tagged = UncheckedCast<i::Type>( \
4372  GetObjectFromRaw(reinterpret_cast<void*>(ptr))); \
4373  /* _As_XXX(..) functions provide storage for TaggedOperatorArrowRef<T> */ \
4374  /* temporary object and return a reference as a measure against gdb */ \
4375  /* error "Attempt to take address of value not located in memory." */ \
4376  static auto result = tagged.operator->(); /* There's no default ctor. */ \
4377  result = tagged.operator->(); \
4378  return result; \
4379  } \
4380  V8_DEBUGGING_EXPORT auto& _As_##Type(i::Tagged<i::HeapObject>& obj) { \
4381  return _As_##Type(obj.ptr()); \
4382  }
4383 
4384 HEAP_OBJECT_ORDINARY_TYPE_LIST(AS_HELPER_DEF)
4385 HEAP_OBJECT_TRUSTED_TYPE_LIST(AS_HELPER_DEF)
4386 ODDBALL_LIST(AS_HELPER_DEF)
4387 #undef AS_HELPER_DEF

4421 V8_DEBUGGING_EXPORT extern "C" void _v8_internal_Print_Code(void* object) {
4422  i::Address address = reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(object);
4423  i::Isolate* isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4424 
4425 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4426  {
4427  if (auto* wasm_code =
4428  i::wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(isolate, address)) {
4429  i::StdoutStream os;
4430  wasm_code->Disassemble(nullptr, os, address);
4431  return;
4432  }
4433  }
4434 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4435 
4436  std::optional<i::Tagged<i::Code>> lookup_result =
4437  isolate->heap()->TryFindCodeForInnerPointerForPrinting(address);
4438  if (!lookup_result.has_value()) {
4439  i::PrintF(
4440  "%p is not within the current isolate's code or embedded spaces\n",
4441  object);
4442  return;
4443  }
4444 
4445 #if defined(OBJECT_PRINT)
4446  i::StdoutStream os;
4447  lookup_result.value()->CodePrint(os, nullptr, address);
4448 #elif defined(ENABLE_DISASSEMBLER)
4449  i::StdoutStream os;
4450  lookup_result.value()->Disassemble(nullptr, os, isolate, address);
4451 #else
4452  i::Print(lookup_result.value());
4453 #endif
4454 }

4464 V8_DEBUGGING_EXPORT extern "C" void _v8_internal_Print_OnlyCode(
4465  void* object, size_t range_limit) {
4466  i::Address address = reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(object);
4467  i::Isolate* isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
4468 
4469 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4470  {
4471  if (i::wasm::GetWasmCodeManager()->LookupCode(isolate, address)) {
4472  i::PrintF("Not supported on wasm code");
4473  return;
4474  }
4475  }
4476 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4477 
4478  std::optional<i::Tagged<i::Code>> lookup_result =
4479  isolate->heap()->TryFindCodeForInnerPointerForPrinting(address);
4480  if (!lookup_result.has_value()) {
4481  i::PrintF(
4482  "%p is not within the current isolate's code or embedded spaces\n",
4483  object);
4484  return;
4485  }
4486 
4487 #if defined(ENABLE_DISASSEMBLER)
4488  i::StdoutStream os;
4489  lookup_result.value()->DisassembleOnlyCode(nullptr, os, isolate, address,
4490  range_limit);
4491 #endif
4492 }

4499 namespace _v8_internal_debugonly {
4500 // This class is easy to navigate in a GUI debugger and not intended for
4501 // use elsewhere.
4502 struct StackTraceDebugDetails {
4503  i::StackFrame::Type type;
4504  std::string summary;
4505  std::vector<i::Tagged<i::SharedFunctionInfo>> functions;
4506  std::vector<i::Tagged<i::Object>> expressions;
4507 };
4508 } // namespace _v8_internal_debugonly
4509 
4510 // Used by lldb_visualizers.py to create a representation of the V8 stack.
4511 V8_DEBUGGING_EXPORT extern std::vector<
4512  _v8_internal_debugonly::StackTraceDebugDetails>
4513 _v8_internal_Expand_StackTrace(i::Isolate* isolate) {
4514  std::vector<_v8_internal_debugonly::StackTraceDebugDetails> stack;
4515  i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4516  int frame_index = 0;
4517 
4518  for (i::StackFrameIterator it(isolate); !it.done(); it.Advance()) {
4519  i::CommonFrame* frame = i::CommonFrame::cast(it.frame());
4520  _v8_internal_debugonly::StackTraceDebugDetails details;
4521  details.type = frame->type();
4522 
4523  if (frame->is_javascript()) {
4524  i::JavaScriptFrame::cast(frame)->GetFunctions(&details.functions);
4525  if (!frame->is_optimized_js()) {
4526  int exprcount = frame->ComputeExpressionsCount();
4527  for (int i = 0; i < exprcount; i++) {
4528  details.expressions.push_back(frame->GetExpression(i));
4529  }
4530  }
4531  }
4532 
4533  i::HandleScope scope(isolate);
4534  i::StringStream::ClearMentionedObjectCache(isolate);
4535  i::HeapStringAllocator allocator;
4536  i::StringStream accumulator(&allocator);
4537  frame->Print(&accumulator, i::StackFrame::OVERVIEW, frame_index++);
4538  std::unique_ptr<char[]> overview = accumulator.ToCString();
4539  details.summary = overview.get();
4540  stack.push_back(std::move(details));
4541  }
4542  return stack;
4543 }

4545 V8_DEBUGGING_EXPORT extern "C" void _v8_internal_Print_TransitionTree(
4546  void* object, bool start_at_root = false) {
4547  i::Tagged<i::Object> o(GetObjectFromRaw(object));
4548  if (!IsMap(o)) {

4551 #if defined(DEBUG) || defined(OBJECT_PRINT)
4552  i::Tagged<i::Map> map = i::UncheckedCast<i::Map>(o);
4553  i::TransitionsAccessor transitions(
4554  i::Isolate::Current(),
4555  start_at_root ? map->FindRootMap(GetPtrComprCageBase(map)) : map);
4556  transitions.PrintTransitionTree();
4557 #endif
4558  }
4559 }
